act.article:
2  In these rules unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context 


a the Act means the Workmen's Compensation Act, 1923 (8 of 1923); 

b authorised officer means any officer whom the State Government may designate either generally or in respect of any area or class of cases, for the purpose of performing the functions assigned by these rules to the authorised officer; 
 2[***] 

c transferring authority means any authority in any   3[***] country who transfers or causes to be transferred any lump sum awarded under the law relating to workmen's compensation in such  4[***] country and applicable for the benefit of any person residing or about to reside in India.
